commit.message:
bug fix IdRealForm for semisimple compact form

IdRealForm for compact real forms has only picked up the first simple summand (this was a relict from an older version that only worked for simple LAs). I have corrected this and now all simple factors are picked up.

commit.message:
Tweak SqrtField_objectify; fix mutability issue

- Declare `SqrtField_objectify` using `BindGlobal`
- Drop `type` argument of `SqrtField_objectify`, it is always SqrtFieldType
- Remove one level of nesting for the `elm` argument to `SqrtField_objectify`:
  so instead of `SqrtField_objectify([x])`, now write `SqrtField_objectify(x)`
- Finally, don't pass an immutable list as second argument to `Objectify`. This
  is trivial to achieve thanks to the previous point.

Note that passing immutable objects as second argument to `Objectify` was
always illegal in GAP, but due to a bug this restriction was not properly
enforced. As a result, code accidentally passing in immutable objects silently
worked. Future versions of GAP will issue a warning for this, and one distant
day perhaps even an error.

In the meantime, this patch prepares corelg for this eventuality, and even if
that day never comes, it does no harm either.

Avoid using DeclareGlobalVariable/InstallValue

The main (only?) reason to use this combination is one needs to read in code
which references the variable before one can possible define the variable.
That's is not the case here.

On the GAP side, there are various issues with `InstallValue`, so on the long
run, some of us are thinking about replacing it with a better mechanism. While
it is not yet clear whether this will happen at all, and in which form,
avoiding its use in corelg means one place less we (the GAP team) have to
worry about it :-)
tst: work around buggy assertion in GAP <= 4.10
Remove duplicate NameRealForm(L) from manual example
